have you ever woke up paralysed and swore you were awake but felt like you were dreaming everytime this happens i feel like there is some sort of presence touching me and forcing me down and sometimes pressing me down into my bed and i get this intense chill sensation that runs down my back i am consciously aware of what going on around me but i feel like i'm dreaming has this happen to anyone else before or is it just me if so do you what this could be it's called sleep paralysis and it's completely normal even though it is often scary some people experience it often for others maybe only a couple times in their whole life the reason for it is really simple when we sleep our brain sends out a signal that basically paralyzes us that way we don't thrash around act out our dreams or hurt ourselves accidentally sometimes we wake up before the paralysis wears off and we find that we cannot move or open our eyes because our breathing is also still on autopilot some people feel as if there is a weight on their chests because they are not controlling their breathing consciously some people hear noises and sometimes those noises are scary even though we are awake these noises are left over from our dream state and when sleep paralysis happens to you you get scared right that's why the noises can turn scary it's totally normal and if you would like to know more about it look up sleep paralysis online at any reputable scientific site hope that helps Lucid dreaming Out-of-body experience Dream Sleep paralysis Traumatic brain injury Milton H. Erickson Narcolepsy Sleep Philosophical skepticism Hypnagogia Insomnia Pok__mon Abilities Consciousness Scenes from a Memory Urinary incontinence Fertility awareness Hypnosis Epilepsy Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Jon Secada Avenue Q A Day in the Life Miss Saigon Sigmund Freud The Shining (film) Shaggy dog story Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Soul Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Prank flash